<section sectnbr = "6C">
<servcat sctnbr = "06" scnbr = "03">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "1">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AFRAP70A6301002" svcinfotypenbr = "03" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Description du fonctionnement des pièces constitutives du système EPS
</title>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "3" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "1.429in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.488in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "4.219in"/>
<thead>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry namest = "1" nameend = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Pièces constitutives du système EPS
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Fonction
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" morerows = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
Ensemble de colonne de direction
</emph>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
Capteur de couple
</emph>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
A l&#39;aide de deux circuits (par exemple, les circuits principal et secondaire), le capteur de couple émet des tensions proportionnelles au couple du braquage et à la direction vers le module de commande P/S.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
Moteur P/S
</emph>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Le moteur P/S produit des couples d&#39;assistance au braquage qui correspondent au courant électrique provenant du module de commande P/S.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry namest = "1" nameend = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
Module de commande P/S
</emph>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Le module de commande P/S commande le courant d&#39;entraînement de moteur P/S en déterminant la quantité et la direction de l&#39;assistance en fonction du signal de tension en provenance du capteur de couple, de la vitesse du véhicule et d&#39;autres données reçues via les communications CAN.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Le module de commande P/S détermine si le moteur est en marche ou non en utilisant le signal de régime moteur transmis par le CAN
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry namest = "1" nameend = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
<emph>
Témoin &#34;P/S&#34;
</emph>
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Le témoin &#34;P/S&#34; s&#39;allume lorsque le système P/S ne fonctionne pas normalement.
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
